Back to SX Futures this weekend in Glendale Arizona with Cole Davies’s

It’s been a massive 2 weeks for him and he’s made some good gains judging by the stopwatch, it never lies someone once told me…

Very fortunate to have the support of so many different people to make this all possible for Cole, it really is an individual sport on Saturday once the gate drops but it takes a massive support network to get to that point of family, friends, sponsors and so on, so thanks to everyone that’s helping to make this happen!

The last 3 days have been rewarding, albeit challenging at times, but to see how far he has come with supercross and especially today through some nasty whoops and over some big rhythm sections was rewarding.

Excited to see if he can convert it all to the race track on Saturday once the sun goes down and the lights come on…

The Yamaha Adventure 2024 is back! The Great Southern Ride is presented to you by Yamaha in conjunction with 101 Adventures. Kicking off in Blenheim, the ride will take you through breath-taking trails and scenery throughout the South Island with nights in Hanmer Springs, Fairlie, Wanaka and finishing up in Invercargill with the option to continue to Ride to the Burt Munro Challenge. All Yamaha road registered adventure bikes are welcome, dates are 3-7 February 2024.

Register now via https://101adventures.co.nz/adv-tours
